column4: <content>Bruegel. Charles de Tolnay, 'A new Miniature by Pieter Bruegel the Elder', Burlington Magazine, June 1978, pp. 393ff. In the John Soanes Museum; illustrated by Giulio Clovio, MS of Commentary on St Paul' Epistles by Marino Grimani, Cardinal of Venice & Patriach of Aquiline. One miniature to be attrb. to P. Br. the Elder (Fig. 65) Folio of the MS miniatures which frame the pope left, top, on right by Clovio to the Soane Museum in left border various animals and 'Weltlandschaft' attrib. by Tolnay to Bruegel (Fig. 66); [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. The landscape looks rather poor. The attrib. to Bruegel very doubtful couldn't it be an attempt by Clovio to imitate Northern landscapes? Tolnay does not give the inv.N° of the MS. Look up the volume at the museum; [verso] Nothing about the colours used. Like Benesch T. tried to rush into print. The miniature is very inferior to the earliest known drawings of Bruegel.</content>
